Case 1:20-cr-00330-AJN Document 763 Filed 08/10/22 Page 108 of 197 2649 LCHCmax3 Dubin - direct
1 MR. PAGLIUCA: No, I'm not asking her about flight records going to the moon.
2 THE COURT: So it does matter what you're asking her about.
3 MR. PAGLIUCA: Of course.
4 THE COURT: So I'll sustain at least on that ground, 401, 403.
5 MR. PAGLIUCA: Okay. I understand.
6 THE COURT: We can take our break.
7 (Recess)
8 THE COURT: So I note, I did, at 11:54, Ms. Menninger, receive an application. I think one of the things I asked for was a proposed order, which I don't see.
9 When would the government like to respond?
10 MS. COMEY: Your Honor, Mr. Rohrbach is currently writing our response. I suspect we can get it to your Honor by the beginning of the lunch break.
11 THE COURT: Thank you. And Mr. Pagliuca, I just want to make sure, we're moving on from the media?
12 MR. PAGLIUCA: Yes.
13 THE COURT: All right.
14 MS. MOE: Very briefly, your Honor, to flag some logistics that Mr. Pagliuca and I worked out. My understanding is that he intends to publish a redacted version flight records --
SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300 DOJ-OGR-00016837
